Wash and dry produce.

Drain @pepper and onion mix{6%ounce}.

Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Dice @tomato{1}(diced).

Dice @mini cucumber{1}(diced). Tear @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(torn).

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #nonstick pan{}.

Cook @ground beef{10%ounce} and pepper and onion mix, breaking up meat, until
browned, ~{2%minutes}. Add garlic, @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}; cook, stirring, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, half the
@BBQ sauce{2%tbsp}, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4); bring to a boil and
cook until beef is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

In a #microwavable rice{} package; snip to partially open. Microwave for
~{90%seconds}. Fluff and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #bowl{}, mix @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and remaining @BBQ sauce{2%tbsp}.

In a second bowl, toss tomato and cucumber; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Top rice with beef, salad, @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}(grated), @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, BBQ mayo, and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges.